column1: #Text=Henry Bourchier , 2nd Earl of Essex , KG , in a procession of Garter Knights , detail from Black Book of the Garter c.1535 .
#Text=On his mantle he displays the arms quarterly : 1st : Bourchier ; 2nd : de Bohun ; [ 2 ]
#Text=3rd : Wydeville , Earl of Rivers ; 4th : Louvain
#Text=Garter stall plate of Henry Bourchier , 2nd Earl of Essex , 3rd Count of Eu ( 1468-1540 ) , 6th Baron Bourchier KG , nominated as a Knight of the Garter in 1499 .
#Text=St George 's Chapel , Windsor Castle .
#Text=Inscribed above : " Le Conte Henri de Esex et de Ew " .
#Text=Arms : Quarterly 1st & 4th :
#Text=Argent , a cross engrailed gules between four water bougets sable ( Bourchier ) ;

#Text=2nd : Gules billety or a fess argent ( Louvain , feudal barons of Little Easton , Essex ( for the maternal grandfather of the 1st Count of Eu , Sir John de Louvain ( d.1347 ) ) ; 3rd : argent a fess and canton gules ( ( Wydville , Earl of Rivers ) ) .
#Text=Crest : A man 's ( Moor 's ) head in profile proper ducally crowned or with a pointed cap gules ; [ 3 ]
#Text=Arms of Sir Henry Bourchier , 2nd Earl of Essex , KG

#Text=Henry Bourchier , 2nd Earl of Essex , 6th Baron Bourchier , 3rd Count of Eu and 2nd Viscount Bourchier KG KB PC ( died 13 March 1540 ) was an English soldier , peer and courtier at the courts of Henry VII and Henry VIII .
#Text=He married Mary Say , by whom he had one daughter , Anne , who became his heir .
#Text=Family
#Text=Bourchier was the son of William Bourchier , Viscount Bourchier and Anne Woodville .
#Text=Through his mother , he was the nephew of Elizabeth Woodville , queen consort to Edward IV .
#Text=He inherited the titles of 2nd Earl of Essex , 6th Baron Bourchier , 3rd Count of Eu and 2nd Viscount Bourchier from his grandfather Henry Bourchier , 1st Earl of Essex on his death in 1483 .
#Text=He married twice , about 1512 to Mary Say(e ) ( 1474-1535 ) , then about 1536 to Mary Blount ( 1498-1555 ) .
#Text=Career
#Text=Bourchier was a member of Henry VII 's privy council .
#Text=He was present at the Siege of Boulogne in 1492 and five years later led a detachment against the rebels at Blackheath .
#Text=When Henry VIII became king , he was made captain of the new bodyguard .
#Text=In 1513 , he commanded the cavalry vanguard at the Battle of the Spurs , where he ordered the charge which routed the French gendarmes .
#Text=As Lieutenant-general of the Spears , he was subsequently present at the sieges of Terouanne and Tournai and was appointed Chief Captain of the King 's forces the following year .
#Text=in 1520 he was part of King Henry 's entourage when he met in France with the French king at the Field of the Cloth of Gold , wher he carried the Sword of State . [ 4 ]
#Text=He was one of the judges at the trial in 1521 of Edward Stafford , 3rd Duke of Buckingham , when the latter was tried on a charge of treason .
#Text=Bourchier received the manor of Bedminster as his share of the Duke 's forfeited estates .
#Text=In March 1540 , he broke his neck after falling from his horse and died from his injury and was buried at Little Easton church in Essex . [ 5 ]
#Text=Without male issue , his earldom and his countship became extinct .

#Text=His barony was inherited by his daughter Anne , who had married William Parr , Baron Parr of Kendal , brother of Queen Katherine Parr , who was created Earl of Essex in 1543 and Marquess of Northampton in 1547 . [ 4 ]
#Text=Anne later separated from her husband .
